WEBVTT

00:03.003 --> 00:04.656
- ♪ Hey, here comes Sunny
keeping it fun ♪

00:04.743 --> 00:06.441
♪ Never says never,
never gives up ♪

00:06.528 --> 00:08.530
♪ It's Sunny,
yeah, she's Sunny ♪

00:08.617 --> 00:10.271
♪ Hey ♪

00:10.358 --> 00:12.055
♪ Gear up and go
in the Glam Van ♪

00:12.142 --> 00:13.796
♪ Hair styling
with her best friends ♪

00:13.883 --> 00:16.103
♪ It's Sunny,
yeah, she's Sunny ♪

00:16.190 --> 00:19.280
♪ Oh, it's a Sunny Day ♪

00:19.367 --> 00:21.543
♪ She'll put a smile
on your face ♪

00:21.630 --> 00:23.371
- Whoo-hoo!

00:23.458 --> 00:28.115
- ♪ Sunny is shining
all the way ♪

00:28.202 --> 00:31.118
♪ Yeah, she's Sunny,
yeah, she's Sunny ♪

00:31.205 --> 00:33.468
♪ Having a sunny, sunny day ♪

00:33.555 --> 00:34.556
- Hoo-hoo!

00:36.036 --> 00:38.864
[upbeat music]

00:38.951 --> 00:42.825
♪ ♪

00:42.912 --> 00:45.132
- Oh, I missed a spot.

00:45.219 --> 00:48.309
♪ ♪

00:48.396 --> 00:51.312
All these papers--
what a mess!

00:51.399 --> 00:53.401
That's better.

00:58.275 --> 01:01.974
Whoops, excuse me!

01:02.062 --> 01:04.977
- You've done a great job
cleaning the salon, Blair.

01:05.065 --> 01:07.893
But maybe it's enough now.
- You're right.

01:07.980 --> 01:09.808
And who cares if
a customer's famous?

01:09.895 --> 01:11.201
It doesn't mean--
- What?

01:11.288 --> 01:12.681
Famous customer?

01:12.768 --> 01:14.987
This place could
never be too clean.

01:15.075 --> 01:17.729
So, who is it?
Wait, don't tell me.

01:17.816 --> 01:20.471
Is it Mandy, or the dog on the
label of the pet food can?

01:20.558 --> 01:22.560
What about--
- Oh, Doodle, it's the--

01:22.647 --> 01:25.302
[door bell jingling]
- [yips]

01:25.389 --> 01:27.217
- [gasps]
all: The Surf Bros!

01:27.304 --> 01:28.653
- That's us.

01:28.740 --> 01:30.481
- Yeah,
here to get our style on

01:30.568 --> 01:32.614
for the big concert
at the park later today,

01:32.701 --> 01:34.529
if there's a concert.

01:34.616 --> 01:38.098
- "If there's a concert"?
Sandy, Shell, what do you mean?

01:38.185 --> 01:40.361
- This morning, I wiped out
while I was surfing.

01:40.448 --> 01:41.797
I hurt my finger.

01:41.884 --> 01:43.668
- Now Shell can barely
hold his drumsticks

01:43.755 --> 01:45.453
without saying, "Ow."
- Ow!

01:45.540 --> 01:47.019
- See?

01:47.107 --> 01:50.762
- So, what you need
is a new drummer, right?

01:50.849 --> 01:52.199
- Yeah.

01:52.286 --> 01:53.809
- Well, you're in luck because

01:53.896 --> 01:56.551
this drumming dog just
happens to be available.

01:56.638 --> 01:59.902
One, two, three, four!
[energetic drum beat]

01:59.989 --> 02:03.166
- Whoa, he's quite
the drum master!

02:03.253 --> 02:05.037
- What's that?
Drum faster?

02:05.125 --> 02:06.691
[laughs]
You got it!

02:06.778 --> 02:07.997
[faster drumming]

02:08.084 --> 02:10.042
[animals whimpering]

02:10.130 --> 02:12.436
- Careful, Doodle,
you don't wanna--

02:12.523 --> 02:15.004
[crash]

02:15.091 --> 02:16.440
- On second thought,

02:16.527 --> 02:18.355
maybe I need
a bit more practice.

02:18.442 --> 02:20.966
- [grunts]

02:21.053 --> 02:22.620
- [sighs] Huh?
[door bell jingling]

02:22.707 --> 02:24.405
- Hello, everybody.

02:24.492 --> 02:26.668
You got bottles?
You got cans?

02:26.755 --> 02:29.018
Just call Timmy, I'm--
[gasps]

02:29.105 --> 02:30.759
The Surf Bros!

02:30.846 --> 02:32.500
- That's us.
- 'Sup.

02:32.587 --> 02:34.415
- Oh...
[giggles]

02:34.502 --> 02:37.157
- Sandy, Shell,
you remember Timmy,

02:37.244 --> 02:39.811
Friendly Falls' very own--

02:39.898 --> 02:42.336
um, what job
is it today, Timmy?

02:42.423 --> 02:45.165
- Recycling guy
at your service.

02:45.252 --> 02:48.037
It's one of my top five
favorite jobs.

02:48.124 --> 02:49.995
- Here's a couple
of empty shampoo bottles.

02:50.082 --> 02:51.388
[gasps]
There's more out back.

02:51.475 --> 02:53.260
I'll go get them.

02:53.347 --> 02:55.914
- Are you guys excited about
your big concert today?

02:56.001 --> 02:58.700
- Actually, we're not sure
there's gonna be--

02:58.787 --> 03:00.267
- Wait, bro, look.

03:00.354 --> 03:01.790
[rhythmic drumming]

03:01.877 --> 03:03.357
You thinking
what I'm thinking?

03:03.444 --> 03:04.967
- Yeah!
I think.

03:05.054 --> 03:07.317
- Here you go, Timmy.

03:07.404 --> 03:09.885
- Thanks, Blair.
Well, see you later.

03:09.972 --> 03:13.671
- Whoa, recycling guy.
- That drumming was awesome.

03:13.758 --> 03:14.890
How'd you like
to be our new drummer?

03:14.977 --> 03:17.675
- [gasps]
Me? Are you kidding?

03:17.762 --> 03:20.635
On my list of all-time
favorite jobs to try,

03:20.722 --> 03:22.724
rock star is number one!

03:22.811 --> 03:25.030
- So you'll do it?Sweet!

03:25.117 --> 03:27.685
- Ow.
- Sorry.

03:27.772 --> 03:30.688
- But I can't.
I have a job to do.

03:30.775 --> 03:32.386
Sorry, Surf Bros,

03:32.473 --> 03:35.693
but recycling doesn't
collect itself, you know.

03:35.780 --> 03:39.828
- Wait, Timmy,
what if we did the recycling?

03:39.915 --> 03:42.309
- Really?
You'd do that for me?

03:42.396 --> 03:44.702
- Sure!
You stay here and rehearse.

03:44.789 --> 03:46.356
We'll come to the park
before the show

03:46.443 --> 03:49.229
and do your rock star
hairstyling in the Glam Van.

03:49.316 --> 03:51.883
- [laughs]
Perfect!

03:51.970 --> 03:55.800
But I just remembered--
besides the recycling,

03:55.887 --> 03:58.455
I might have one or two
other tiny things

03:58.542 --> 04:00.283
that need doing today.

04:00.370 --> 04:01.763
- No problem.
- Great.

04:01.850 --> 04:04.113
Let me get my list out.

04:04.200 --> 04:05.549
- [groans]

04:05.636 --> 04:08.552
- It's okay.
We can handle it.

04:08.639 --> 04:10.293
- Thanks!
That's really kind of you.

04:10.380 --> 04:12.730
Here it is.
- You got it.

04:12.817 --> 04:14.515
It'll be fun.

04:14.602 --> 04:16.430
Ready, set...
[belt whooshing]

04:16.517 --> 04:19.781
girls: Gear up and go!

04:19.868 --> 04:23.741
- Okay, let's practice.

04:23.828 --> 04:25.830
- You sure
we can do this, Sunny?

04:25.917 --> 04:28.572
That's one looong list.

04:28.659 --> 04:30.444
- Timmy was gonna
do it by himself,

04:30.531 --> 04:31.880
and there are three of us.

04:31.967 --> 04:34.448
- [barks, whimpers]

04:34.535 --> 04:36.972
- Sorry, Rosie.
You're right.

04:37.059 --> 04:39.757
Six of us!
How hard can it be?

04:39.844 --> 04:43.152
♪ ♪

04:43.239 --> 04:44.936
[engine roars]

04:48.679 --> 04:50.681
- Thank you.
Buh-bye!

04:50.768 --> 04:53.597
- You're welcome.
- Bye, Cindy.

04:53.684 --> 04:57.340
♪ ♪

04:57.427 --> 05:01.213
- Phew,
our last recycling pickup.

05:01.301 --> 05:03.259
- Here, let me help.

05:03.346 --> 05:05.783
[girls gasp]
- Oh, oops.

05:05.870 --> 05:08.177
[laughs]
Looks like my tail got thirsty.

05:08.264 --> 05:09.831
[grunts]

05:09.918 --> 05:11.876
Why is that
recycling bin green?

05:11.963 --> 05:15.880
I thought they were blue.
- Green bins are for compost

05:15.967 --> 05:20.058
like leftover fruit
and vegetable peels.

05:20.145 --> 05:22.147
- Rox, look out for the--
- Hey!

05:22.234 --> 05:24.062
Whoa!
[screams]

05:24.149 --> 05:26.543
- Uh-oh.[grunts]

05:26.630 --> 05:30.199
- Banana peel.
- [sighs]

05:30.286 --> 05:31.896
- Mmm, lunch.

05:31.983 --> 05:34.508
[laughter]

05:37.162 --> 05:39.643
- [sighs]
That's the last one.

05:39.730 --> 05:42.429
- I'm exhausted.
- Oh, Doodle.

05:42.516 --> 05:44.344
[barks]

05:44.431 --> 05:47.042
[energetic music playing]

05:47.129 --> 05:51.829
♪ ♪

05:51.916 --> 05:54.615
- [laughing] Whoa.
That sounded great, Timmy.

05:54.702 --> 05:58.532
- I think I'm getting the hang
of this rock star thing.

05:58.619 --> 06:00.577
Whoops!
[drum sticks clattering]

06:00.664 --> 06:02.231
Whoa!
[laughs]

06:02.318 --> 06:05.365
Or maybe I still need
a little more practice.

06:05.452 --> 06:07.758
And a one, two, three, four.

06:07.845 --> 06:12.415
♪ ♪

06:12.502 --> 06:15.200
- So I decided,
goodbye, green.

06:15.287 --> 06:17.942
My new favorite color
is orange.

06:18.029 --> 06:19.335
But I've been talking
way too much.

06:19.422 --> 06:21.772
I wanna hear
what you think, KC.

06:21.859 --> 06:23.948
- Really?
Well, my favorite is--

06:24.035 --> 06:27.430
- Hold on, that sounds like...

06:27.517 --> 06:30.302
both: [gasp]
The Surf Bros!

06:30.390 --> 06:32.261
[door bell jingling]

06:32.348 --> 06:33.697
- Hey, visitors.

06:33.784 --> 06:35.307
Sorry, were we
playing too loud?

06:35.395 --> 06:36.961
- Not at all.

06:37.048 --> 06:39.050
It's just not every day that
we have the chance

06:39.137 --> 06:42.967
to meet the actual Surf Bros!

06:43.054 --> 06:46.057
And Timmy.
What are you doing here?

06:46.144 --> 06:48.799
- I'm playing drums
in the big concert today.

06:48.886 --> 06:50.192
Whoa!
[laughs]

06:50.279 --> 06:51.541
- Today?

06:51.628 --> 06:54.022
But don't you need to be
rock-star ready?

06:54.109 --> 06:55.676
- It's okay.

06:55.763 --> 06:57.982
Sunny's gonna style us
later at the park.

06:58.069 --> 07:00.768
- Later?
Oh, that Sunny.

07:00.855 --> 07:04.380
Big-time stars like you two--
and Timmy--

07:04.467 --> 07:06.991
shouldn't have
to wait for later.

07:07.078 --> 07:10.168
- You guys are lucky
Lacey came by.

07:10.255 --> 07:11.909
- Uh, we are?

07:11.996 --> 07:14.912
- Oh, yes.
Let's get styling!

07:19.439 --> 07:22.790
- Time for the next job on
Timmy's list--the shoe store.

07:22.877 --> 07:25.532
- Hi, everyone.
What a nice surprise.

07:25.619 --> 07:27.447
- Hi, Riz.

07:27.534 --> 07:32.321
We're helping Timmy today,
so we're to make your new sign.

07:32.408 --> 07:36.847
- Oh, well, then follow me.

07:36.934 --> 07:39.546
The new sign will go
right over here.

07:39.633 --> 07:42.331
I want it to be something
fun and different.

07:42.418 --> 07:43.767
- Well, you're in luck,

07:43.854 --> 07:46.161
'cause nobody's
more fun than us.

07:46.248 --> 07:48.424
- And different.

07:48.511 --> 07:51.514
- Rox, we can use some of your
hair color to paint the sign.

07:51.601 --> 07:54.169
- Got it and on it.
Come on, Doodle.

07:54.256 --> 07:56.301
- Blair, what do you think
about glitter for the--

07:56.388 --> 07:57.781
- [squeals]
- Blair?

07:57.868 --> 07:59.261
- [giggles]

07:59.348 --> 08:02.394
Look at those pink boots
with flowers!

08:02.482 --> 08:04.832
And those silver sneakers
with wings!

08:04.919 --> 08:06.790
Riz, can I try them on?

08:06.877 --> 08:08.488
- Sure, Blair.
Right this way.

08:08.575 --> 08:11.795
- [squeals, giggles]
Yes.

08:11.882 --> 08:13.754
- Blair won't
be back for a while,

08:13.841 --> 08:15.886
but the rest of us can
make the sign, right?

08:15.973 --> 08:18.193
- [barks]
Gear up and...

08:18.280 --> 08:20.151
both: Go!

08:20.238 --> 08:21.501
- [blabbers]

08:21.588 --> 08:24.155
- Doodle and I
got the supplies.

08:24.242 --> 08:29.378
- I'm thinking we draw a huge,
colorful, glittery shoe.

08:29.465 --> 08:30.988
- Great idea, Sunny.

08:31.075 --> 08:34.731
A shoe for a shoe store--
I see what you did there.

08:34.818 --> 08:37.473
[markers squeaking]

08:37.560 --> 08:41.477
- Splashes of color and lots
of glitter to make it sparkle.

08:41.564 --> 08:43.305
[laughter]

08:43.392 --> 08:45.786
- Sparkle and shine!

08:45.873 --> 08:48.702
Wow.
- Looking good, team.

08:48.789 --> 08:50.399
- Uh-huh!

08:50.486 --> 08:53.533
Oh...
[laughs]

08:53.620 --> 08:55.665
Mmm.
Yummy.

08:58.233 --> 09:00.104
- [babbles]

09:03.151 --> 09:05.545
- Maybe if we added
some stickers or--

09:05.632 --> 09:08.025
- Oh!
[grunts]

09:10.506 --> 09:13.509
- [babbles mockingly]

09:13.596 --> 09:15.990
- Hey!
[babbles]

09:17.426 --> 09:18.775
- Oh!
- Whoa!

09:18.862 --> 09:20.385
[both shouting]

09:20.472 --> 09:23.084
- Oh no!
- Hey, that's Violet's carrot!

09:23.171 --> 09:25.042
- Watch out!
Doodle, stop!

09:25.129 --> 09:27.131
- Violet!

09:28.655 --> 09:31.048
- Ha!
- Whoa!

09:33.355 --> 09:35.313
- Did it!
- [squeaks]

09:35.400 --> 09:36.793
[babbles]

09:39.535 --> 09:42.059
- Mm.
Uh-oh.

09:42.146 --> 09:43.626
Aww.

09:43.713 --> 09:45.280
- [gasps]
- Remind me.

09:45.367 --> 09:48.457
Did Riz ask for a big,
colorful, glitter mess?

09:48.544 --> 09:50.459
- It's okay.
We can start over.

09:50.546 --> 09:52.592
But we better hurry.
[door whooshes]

09:54.637 --> 09:56.291
- Whoa, what's this?

09:56.378 --> 09:57.945
- We, uh,

09:58.032 --> 10:01.513
were making your sign and...

10:01.601 --> 10:04.168
- And you did a great job.
I love it!

10:04.255 --> 10:06.997
The footprints are awesome--
perfect for a shoe store.

10:07.084 --> 10:09.478
Fun and different--
exactly what I wanted.

10:09.565 --> 10:11.828
[all cheering]

10:13.264 --> 10:14.875
- I love it!
Thanks, everyone.

10:14.962 --> 10:16.354
- You're very welcome.

10:16.441 --> 10:19.967
- Have a sunny day!

10:20.054 --> 10:22.317
Let's see what's next
on Timmy's list.

10:22.404 --> 10:24.885
"Pick six bushels of apples."

10:24.972 --> 10:27.148
- To the apple orchard!

10:28.976 --> 10:30.281
[energetic music playing]

10:30.368 --> 10:33.415
- [off-tune singing]

10:34.459 --> 10:35.983
[music stops]

10:36.070 --> 10:39.073
- [off-tune singing continues]

10:39.160 --> 10:42.032
Wow, we sound great!

10:42.119 --> 10:45.209
- Um, yeah, except how
am I supposed to play

10:45.296 --> 10:47.690
with all these ribbons
you put on my guitar?

10:47.777 --> 10:50.040
- With style, that's how!

10:50.127 --> 10:51.476
[drum sting]

10:51.563 --> 10:53.261
- Lacey,

10:53.348 --> 10:55.393
I think Sandy, Shell, and I
should head to the park.

10:55.480 --> 10:58.048
The concert's starting soon.

10:58.135 --> 11:01.051
- [gasps] Timmy,
I never realized it before,

11:01.138 --> 11:04.272
but your wardrobe
is a cry for help.

11:04.359 --> 11:05.708
If you're going on stage,

11:05.795 --> 11:08.232
you need a real
rock star outfit!

11:08.319 --> 11:11.714
Hmm...
I've got it!

11:11.801 --> 11:14.325
- Okay.

11:14.412 --> 11:18.025
- Phew--recycling,
sign painting, apple picking.

11:18.112 --> 11:20.375
How many jobs can
Timmy do in a day?

11:20.462 --> 11:24.074
- We'll never finish it all
before the concert starts.

11:24.161 --> 11:25.685
- Never say never.

11:25.772 --> 11:30.385
We'll just have to work
faster and smarter.

11:30.472 --> 11:33.649
[grunting]

11:33.736 --> 11:37.740
Rox, Blair, Doodle, can you
stretch out this hair net?

11:37.827 --> 11:39.524
Pull!

11:39.611 --> 11:41.265
[all grunting]

11:41.352 --> 11:44.529
[branch rustling]
[all cheering]

11:44.616 --> 11:47.402
[bright music]

11:47.489 --> 11:50.013
- [babbling]

11:50.100 --> 11:56.672
♪ ♪

11:56.759 --> 11:58.152
- Nice work, everyone.

11:58.239 --> 12:00.502
That's Timmy's list all done!

12:00.589 --> 12:03.810
Now let's load up these apples
and get to the concert.

12:05.289 --> 12:06.987
- If you're going
to be a rock star,

12:07.074 --> 12:10.947
we'll need some towels
and some aprons,

12:11.034 --> 12:14.908
some foils,
and some scrunchies,

12:14.995 --> 12:18.607
hair pins--ooh, and these.

12:18.694 --> 12:21.828
- Ooh.
- Ta-da!

12:21.915 --> 12:25.483
- Wow.
Just...wow.

12:25.570 --> 12:27.398
- Aww, you're welcome.

12:27.485 --> 12:31.141
Try it on and I'll fix
Sandy and Shell's hair.

12:31.228 --> 12:34.101
- Thanks, but we just need
a quick wash and trim.

12:34.188 --> 12:35.580
Nothing major.

12:35.667 --> 12:37.234
- Quick wash,
total makeover,

12:37.321 --> 12:39.584
all the same thing.
- Whoa!

12:39.671 --> 12:41.282
- Now, let's hurry.
Surf Bros: Huh?

12:41.369 --> 12:43.371
- Time's a-wasting!
- Oh.

12:45.286 --> 12:47.462
- Wow, big crowd.

12:47.549 --> 12:50.552
crowd: [chanting]
We want The Surf Bros!

12:52.728 --> 12:55.992
- The Surf Bros
aren't here yet?

12:57.385 --> 12:59.343
- Okay, I'm ready.

13:02.477 --> 13:04.435
- [squeals]
I love it!

13:04.522 --> 13:06.089
It's fabulous, right?

13:06.176 --> 13:07.525
- Fabulous.

13:07.612 --> 13:08.962
- Well, to be honest,

13:09.049 --> 13:11.355
it's a little tight here
in the pants.

13:11.442 --> 13:13.618
- Pish posh, it's perfect.

13:13.705 --> 13:15.620
Sandy, Shell,
back me up on this.

13:15.707 --> 13:18.449
- We'd be happy to
if we could see anything.

13:18.536 --> 13:20.451
- Oh!
Yep.

13:20.538 --> 13:22.105
Zero visibility.

13:22.192 --> 13:24.064
You'd better drive
to the park, Timmy.

13:24.151 --> 13:26.066
- Mm-kay.
Let me get my keys and the--

13:26.153 --> 13:28.633
[pants ripping]
Oh.

13:28.720 --> 13:30.418
- Huh?

13:30.505 --> 13:32.289
- Oopsie.

13:32.376 --> 13:35.553
crowd: [chanting]
We want The Surf Bros!

13:35.640 --> 13:37.120
- [grunts, sighs]

13:37.207 --> 13:38.992
I never want to see
another apple,

13:39.079 --> 13:41.342
not ever, ever again!

13:41.429 --> 13:44.824
Well, okay, maybe this one.

13:44.911 --> 13:48.175
crowd: [chanting]
We want The Surf Bros!

13:49.132 --> 13:51.221
- Huh?
- Who are those guys?

13:53.136 --> 13:56.618
- Hello, Friendly Falls!

13:56.705 --> 13:59.055
- Oh--are you
ready to rock?

13:59.142 --> 14:02.102
- Hey, those aren't
The Surf Bros.

14:02.189 --> 14:06.019
crowd: [chanting]
We want The Surf Bros!

14:06.106 --> 14:07.934
- Don't you love
their new style?

14:08.021 --> 14:10.110
Lacey did it all by herself.

14:10.197 --> 14:12.939
- No need to thank me,
but I know you'll insist,

14:13.026 --> 14:15.419
so you're welcome.

14:15.506 --> 14:18.683
- Oh no,
those are The Surf Bros,

14:18.770 --> 14:22.078
but with their new hairstyles,
nobody recognizes them!

14:22.165 --> 14:24.472
crowd: We want The Surf Bros!

14:24.559 --> 14:27.779
- Whoo-hoo!
Go Surf Bros!

14:27.867 --> 14:30.260
We're their stylists.

14:30.347 --> 14:32.219
What?
- Where are The Surf Bros?

14:32.306 --> 14:34.264
- Aww, I came here
for The Surf Bros.

14:34.351 --> 14:37.702
crowd: [chanting]
We want The Surf Bros!

14:37.789 --> 14:39.052
- Tough crowd.

14:39.139 --> 14:42.707
Being a rock star
isn't as fun as I thought.

14:42.794 --> 14:45.449
- This is not good.

14:48.757 --> 14:49.976
crowd: [chanting]
We want The Surf Bros!

14:50.063 --> 14:52.326
- I don't get it.
We're right here.

14:52.413 --> 14:55.198
- I don't think they
recognize us, bro.

14:55.285 --> 14:57.113
Let's get out of here.
- Oh!

14:57.200 --> 14:59.072
I can't see a thing.

14:59.159 --> 15:02.162
- [sighs]

15:02.249 --> 15:03.598
- I have an idea.

15:03.685 --> 15:05.469
If I fix
Sandy and Shell's hair,

15:05.556 --> 15:07.515
the audience
will know it's them.

15:07.602 --> 15:10.431
crowd: [chanting]
We want The Surf Bros!

15:10.518 --> 15:13.390
- There's no time.
- Oh, they're gonna leave.

15:13.477 --> 15:16.480
- Not if we keep them busy.
Any ideas?

15:16.567 --> 15:19.483
- The only thing I do have
is lots of apples.

15:19.570 --> 15:22.356
- Apples, that's it!
Great thinking, Blair.

15:22.443 --> 15:25.402
- It is?
Oh, you're welcome.

15:25.489 --> 15:27.883
- Let's hand these apples
out to the crowd.

15:27.970 --> 15:30.190
That'll keep them busy
for a while.

15:30.277 --> 15:33.497
- I got this.
Hello, people!

15:33.584 --> 15:36.805
Come get your apples!

15:36.892 --> 15:38.676
- [groans]
If only there was a way

15:38.763 --> 15:41.288
to get the apples
to the people.

15:41.375 --> 15:45.335
- There is--
super springy hair scrunchies,

15:45.422 --> 15:48.512
our very own apple launchers.

15:49.557 --> 15:52.429
Apples away!
- We want--

15:52.516 --> 15:55.258
whoa, apples!
[crowd cheering, laughing]

15:55.345 --> 15:58.261
[bright music]

15:58.348 --> 16:01.612
♪ ♪

16:01.699 --> 16:03.310
- Ooh, apples!

16:03.397 --> 16:05.094
- This is incredible!
- Whoa!

16:05.181 --> 16:07.618
- Apples are
falling from the sky!

16:07.705 --> 16:10.230
- You guys keep the
crowd busy with apples.

16:10.317 --> 16:14.234
I'm gonna make The Surf Bros
look like The Surf Bros again.

16:15.583 --> 16:17.237
- They say
they want The Surf Bros,

16:17.324 --> 16:20.153
but we are The Surf Bros,
aren't we?

16:20.240 --> 16:21.589
- [gasps]
Oh.

16:21.676 --> 16:22.894
- Sorry, didn't see you there.

16:22.982 --> 16:24.896
Hey, does anybody
know where Sunny is?

16:24.984 --> 16:26.942
We were supposed to
meet her before the show.

16:27.029 --> 16:29.945
- [laughing]
Uh, I'm right here, Sandy.

16:30.032 --> 16:31.947
- All right.
Hi, Sunny.

16:32.034 --> 16:33.601
- [laughs]
- Ow.

16:33.688 --> 16:37.866
- Sorry.
So, Lacey's handiwork?

16:37.953 --> 16:39.999
- Yeah, she did a--

16:40.086 --> 16:42.653
well, interesting job.

16:42.740 --> 16:45.917
My outfit's a little,
uh, breezy.

16:46.005 --> 16:48.007
And Sandy and Shell
can't exactly see

16:48.094 --> 16:49.965
behind those hairstyles.

16:50.052 --> 16:51.967
- No problem.

16:52.054 --> 16:55.449
Wash, trim, and you'll be back
to your usual style in no time.

16:55.536 --> 16:57.364
- Awesome!
- Yes!

16:57.451 --> 17:00.367
[upbeat music]

17:00.454 --> 17:01.803
♪ ♪

17:01.890 --> 17:04.675
First, we need to
get rid of these.

17:04.762 --> 17:09.898
♪ ♪

17:09.985 --> 17:11.726
Then a quick spritz...

17:20.778 --> 17:24.304
- We can see again!
- And we're us again.

17:24.391 --> 17:26.088
Thanks, Sunny.
- No problem.

17:26.175 --> 17:29.700
Now it's time for you three
to get out there and rock.

17:29.787 --> 17:32.877
- Yeah, but first, uh,
could you fix something

17:32.964 --> 17:35.271
